            "bulletPoint": "Christmas Lights Installation, Maintenance, and Removal",
            "description": {
              "en": "Install Christmas lights annually in Broseley Town, including specific installations: 23 sets of pea lights in the memorial garden, 1 set of lights to the fir tree in the memorial garden, 1 set of pea lights to the tree on the square, features to poles in the memorial garden, a 'welcome to Broseley' sign across the high street, festoons to Harwood's building and the butcher's shop, string lights from church street to the social club, and 2 snow fall column motifs. Maintain the lights throughout the installation period with scheduled maintenance run-throughs and call-out services for major faults within 24 hours. Dismantle and remove all lights after the festival period, as soon after 6 January each year as possible, but no later than 12 January each year. The contractor must be present on Saturday 28 November 2026 to manually switch on the lights after a countdown, and after switch-on, set automatic timers (on at 4pm and off at 10pm weekdays, 4pm to 11pm weekends)."
