          {
            "bulletPoint": "Tender Submission and Evaluation Criteria",
            "description": {
              "en": "Submit a tender in writing in a sealed marked envelope addressed to the Town Clerk, clearly marked 'Tender'. The tender must be fully inclusive of all costs, including any costs arising from site visits and access arrangements. Provide evidence of ability to deliver similar projects to a high quality, satisfactory references, and a price within budget. Offer quality and value for money. Provide a copy of the current public liability insurance certificate, Highway Electrical Registration Scheme certificate, LED product details and warranty, and any other pertinent documents or certificates. All invitations to tender are subject to the Town Council's Standing Order number 17 and the terms of the Bribery Act 2010. No contractor shall contact councillors or staff outside the prescribed process. Tenders will be opened by the Town Clerk in the presence of at least two councillors after the deadline, considered at a properly convened meeting on 9 June 2026, and all tenders will receive a response week commencing 15 June 2026."
            },
